<br>
When I was sworn into the Navy, I asked my recruiter about swearing to God, as I'm agnostic.  He said that the swearing in process allows someone not willing to &quot;swear to God&quot; to say &quot;on my honor&quot; instead of &quot;so help me God&quot; (or other variation).  <br>
<br>
